Package com.github.mavolin.maxon.jsonvalues

Class JsonObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.mavolin.maxon.jsonvalues.JsonObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JsonValue
    public class JsonObject
extends java.lang.Object
implements JsonValue
    A JsonObject is a map-like representation of a JSON object. Every object consists of a key and value, where the key represents the name of the variable stored, and the value its data. A value can be of all JSON types, and just as in Java JSON objects can store inner objects.

      • keySet

        public java.util.Set<java.lang.String> keySet()
        Returns a Set view of the keys contained in this JsonObject. The set is backed by the JsonObject, so changes to the JsonObject are reflected in the set, and vice-versa. If the JsonObject is modified while an iteration over the set is in progress (except through the iterator's own remove operation), the results of the iteration are undefined. The set supports element removal, which removes the corresponding JsonObjectping from the JsonObject, via the Iterator.remove, Set.remove, removeAll, retainAll, and clear operations. It does not support the add or addAll operations.
        Returns:
        a set view of the keys contained in this JsonObject

      • values

        public java.util.Collection<JsonElement> values()
        Returns a Collection view of the values contained in this JsonObject. The collection is backed by the JsonObject, so changes to the JsonObject are reflected in the collection, and vice-versa. If the JsonObject is modified while an iteration over the collection is in progress (except through the iterator's own remove operation), the results of the iteration are undefined. The collection supports element removal, which removes the corresponding JsonObjectping from the JsonObject, via the Iterator.remove, Collection.remove, removeAll, retainAll and clear operations. It does not support the add or addAll operations.
        Returns:
        a collection view of the values contained in this JsonObject

      • entrySet

        public java.util.Set<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,​JsonElement>> entrySet()
        Returns a Set view of the JsonObjectpings contained in this JsonObject. The set is backed by the JsonObject, so changes to the JsonObject are reflected in the set, and vice-versa. If the JsonObject is modified while an iteration over the set is in progress (except through the iterator's own remove operation, or through the setValue operation on a JsonObject entry returned by the iterator) the results of the iteration are undefined. The set supports element removal, which removes the corresponding JsonObjectping from the JsonObject, via the Iterator.remove, Set.remove, removeAll, retainAll and clear operations. It does not support the add or addAll operations.
        Returns:
        a set view of the JsonObjectpings contained in this JsonObject
